.TH "KENNEL-AKC" "8" "" "Project Kennel" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
kennel\-akc \- sshd AuthorizedKeysCommand helper
.SH SYNOPSIS
(internal \(em forked by kenneld(8), not invoked directly)
.SH DESCRIPTION
kennel\-akc is the root\-owned AuthorizedKeysCommand helper for the per\-kennel SSH egress bastion. sshd invokes it to fetch the synthetic public key for a connecting kennel; it queries the running kenneld. Bindings live only in kenneld \(em there is no authorized_keys file.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBkenneld\fR(8), \fBkennel\fR(1)
